result.execSummary:
The defendant Ashley J. McGargill was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possess Methamphetamine Precursors, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.65.
  • Bail Jumping-Felony, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes:
Defendant was granted 77 days credit for time served.
Concurrent with: Prison term on Ct 4 in this same case, but consecutive to jail sentence on Cts 1 & 2 in case 15CF129

superMiscConds.notes: Defendant is ordered to pay the DNA surcharge, and to make arrangements to provide a DNA sample, within 48 hours, for testing through the Clark County Sheriff Department or if on probation, to the Department of Corrections as is required in all criminal convictions.  Costs paid out of bond.

Defendant shall attend counseling, treatments, programming, evaluations as deemed appropriate by the agent releasing all records to the agent upon request
Defendant to undergo a psychological evaluation and follow all recommendations releasing all records to her agent.

Defendant shall not possess or consume any alcohol, and not go into places that sell alcohol except incidentally such as a grocery store, convenience store or gas station or other such place where alcohol is not sold for consumption on the premises.
Defendant shall not possess or consume any medication or drug except as may be specifically prescribed by a medical professional for defendant, and then shall be taken only as prescribed.
he defendant shall have no contact with Cedric Riggins or Chad Schoolmaster  of any kind, whether direct or indirect, including in person, in writing, by phone, by e-mail or other electronic means, through a third party or in any other way.  Defendant may have contact through attorney's involved or through court hearing regarding money owed and/or possessions.  
Defendant is not to have contact with any individual who is using, selling or manufacturing any drugs.
AMENDED 05/31/2019 No contact with Chad Schoolmaster is lifted if written approval by the supervising agent is received by the Court.

The defendant shall pay Department of Correction fees as directed by the agent.  The defendant shall submit to random urine/PBT testing as required by the agent or any law enforcement officer.
Electronic monitoring may be used if deemed appropriate by the agent.
The defendant is to submit to an Alcohol and Other Drug Assessment (AODA) and follow the recommendations, releasing the findings to the agent.
